OL,3,CTory peer facing three-week suspension
OL,4,Cfor calling colleague 'Lord Poppadom'
OL,6,FA baroness is facing a three-week
OL,7,Fsuspension from the House of Lords for
OL,8,Fcalling a British-Asian peer "Lord
OL,9,FPoppadom", and touching the hair of a
OL,10,FBlack female MP.
OL,12,FComplaints were made about Baroness
OL,13,FMeyer about two separate incidents
OL,14,Fduring a visit of the Joint Committee
OL,15,Fon Human Rights to Rwanda in February
OL,16,Fthis year.
OL,18,FShe was found to have twice called
OL,19,FLord Dholakia "Lord Poppadom", and to
OL,20,Fhave touched the hair of Labour MP
OL,21,FBell Ribeiro-Addy without consent.
