OL,3,CTory peer facing three-week suspension
OL,4,Cfor calling colleague 'Lord Poppadom'
OL,6,FThe report into her conduct says that
OL,7,Fduring the trip to Rwanda, she
OL,8,Fmistakenly address Lord Dholakia as
OL,9,F"Lord Popat" - another South Asian
OL,10,Fmember of the Lords. It says she
OL,11,F"immediately apologised", but other
OL,12,Fmembers of the party in the taxi said
OL,13,Fthey heard her twice call him "Lord
OL,14,FPoppadom".
OL,16,FLord Dholakia says he didn't hear the
OL,17,Fremarks himself, but the watchdog said
OL,18,Fother members of the group did.
