OL,3,CTory peer facing three-week suspension
OL,4,Cfor calling colleague 'Lord Poppadom'
OL,6,FBaroness Meyer initially denied the
OL,7,Faccusations, calling them "unfounded
OL,8,Fand baseless", but later admitted "it
OL,9,Fis possible I said it, but I don't
OL,10,Fremember", as she had drunk "possibly
OL,11,Fthree glasses of wine".
OL,13,FThe complaint by Ribeiro-Addy said
OL,14,Fthat one evening on the trip Baroness
OL,15,FMeyer complimented her hair and asked
OL,16,Fif she could touch it - "without
OL,17,Fwaiting for a reply or for permission
OL,18,FLady Meyer then reached out and lifted
OL,19,Fone of Ms Ribeiro-Addy's braids".
