OL,3,CTory peer facing three-week suspension
OL,4,Cfor calling colleague 'Lord Poppadom'
OL,6,FThe commissioner had said: "Due to the
OL,7,Fsignificance of Baroness Meyer's
OL,8,Fbreach of the Code of Conduct and the
OL,9,Fimpact of her behaviour on the
OL,10,Fcomplainants, I consider a short
OL,11,Fsuspension to be justified in the
OL,12,Fcircumstances.
OL,14,F"I also consider that behaviour
OL,15,Ftraining would be beneficial for
OL,16,FBaroness Meyer, to address the
OL,17,Fspecific behaviour in this case. I
OL,18,Ftherefore recommend that Baroness
OL,19,FMeyer undertake bespoke behaviour
OL,20,Ftraining provided by an approved
OL,21,Fexternal provider."
